title: Most valuable Swedish brands 2019
summary: The Most valuable Swedish in the brands 2019 was Swedish Volvo , who made 21531 million .
The most valuable Swedish was Telia , with just 2404 million .

In second place was Swedish H&M with 15876 million ; third place went to Swedish IKEA with 21531 million ; fourth place went to Swedish Absolut with 2404 million and fifth place went to Swedish Nordea , who was 5638 million .
gold: As of 2019 , the self-assembly furniture retailer IKEA was the most valuable Swedish brand . The company 's value amounted to over 21 billion U.S. dollars that year . H & M ( short for Hennes & Mauritz ) came second , with a value of nearly 16 billion U.S. dollars .
